children.name: Your styles will be transformed into style design tokens automatically. To avoid styles from being exported prefix them with a ‘_’ (underscore). This prefix can be changed in the plugin settings.
children.characters:
Your styles will be transformed into style design tokens automatically.
To avoid styles from being exported prefix them with a ‘_’ (underscore). This prefix can be changed in the plugin settings.

children.name: The “File Export settings” window allows you to manage settings that are used when exporting tokens to a json file. It also allows you to start the export to file. You can read more about the settings in the documentation.

children.name: To create design tokens for values that can not be stored as a style you can create a frame with a name starting with _tokens.  Any main component inside the frame can be a custom token. By following a naming convention the plugin can find out what property should be exported.
children.characters:
To create design tokens for values that can not be stored as a style you can create a frame with a name starting with _tokens.  Any main component inside the frame can be a custom token. 
By following a naming convention the plugin can find out what property should be exported.
